SHORT="graphical user interface for eaay manipulation of ISO images"
cat << EOF
KIso is a graphical user interface for KDE 3.x which has the purpose to make it
as easy as possible to: 

* Create ISO images from a CD.
* Create new own ISO images.
* Open ISO and NRG images to read it's content.
* Extract ISO and NRG images.
* Edit the content of ISO Images.
* Convert BIN/CUE images to ISO images.
EOF
